Package the existing local Node.js web application for macOS without Electron or Docker.

Requirements:

- Use Node.js Single Executable Applications (SEA) to create a standalone backend executable.
- Do not require Node.js, npm, or Docker on the target Mac.
- Keep frontend and backend source-code changes minimal.
- Build the frontend for production and bundle its generated files with the application.
- Start the backend automatically on "127.0.0.1" only.
- Open the application URL automatically in the user’s default browser.
- Wrap the executable inside a standard macOS ".app" bundle so users can launch it by double-clicking in Finder.
- Stop the backend cleanly when the application exits.
- Support both Apple Silicon ("arm64") and Intel ("x64") builds.
- Add build scripts and document the complete packaging process.
- Do not add analytics, auto-updates, remote URLs, or external network dependencies.
- Produce distributable ZIP files for each architecture.
- Clearly document any limitations involving macOS Gatekeeper, code signing, and notarization.